x4freetext: External deuteron beam of U-120M.
Cylindrical NE213-equivalent liquid scintillator
BC5O1A BICRON 2inch in diameter and 2inch in length,
optically coupled to PMT Hamamatsu R329-02. To cover
dynamic range of registered neutron from 0.7 to 35 MeV,
pulse-height spectra were registered at two values of
PMT supply (1500 and 2200 V).
Detector response and efficiency were calculated using
Monte Carlo code SCINFUL-R and tested by calibrated
Cf-252 neutron source.
Detector was housed in double-conical iron collimator
and in shield of iron, borated polyethylene and lead.
Neutron spectrometer was operated with
two-dimensional n-g discrimination hardware. List-mode
registration of pulse-height and monitoring events in
external buffer permits to perform dead-time and
systematical error corrections. Employing off-line
Gaussian analysis of two-dimensional pulse height
spectra, a complete discrimination between neutrons and
photons was achieved above recoil proton energy 0.7MeV.
Neutron spectra were obtained from pulse-height
distribution of recoils by unfolding code GRAVEL.
Absolute normalization was performed by
measuring of d-beam charge in electrically isolated
thick Li target or in Faraday cup which collected
deuterons passed thin Li target.
Uncertainty of detector efficiency   4-6%
Uncertainty of d-beam charge on target  <2%
Uncertainty of correction for dead-time <1%
Statistical uncertainty from pulse-height
statistics, errors of background subtraction and (n,g)
discrimination procedure was generated by deconvolution
process and simulation of detector response function.
Data were provided by P.Bem in March 2020.
Compiled by SS

x4freetext: Deuteron beam was focused on thick Li-nat target of
40 mm in diameter and 6 mm overall thickness sufficient
to stop incident deuterons. Target consisted of 1.5 mm
metallic foil (density 0.534 g/cm2) pressurized into
stainless steel chamber (wall thickness of 2 mm)
in argon atmosphere.
Naohiko Otsuka (2020-03-21):
There is an additional TTY data set at Ed=17.0 MeV
and 120 deg on Fig.4 of ISINN-12 Conf. Proc. p168.,
but Pavel Bem recommends not to include it in the
EXFOR entry.

x4freetext: Self-supporting metallic foil of enriched Li-7 (< 0.05%
of 6Li) with the thickness of 0.5(+/-10%) mm insured by
provider (Plant of Chemical Extracts, Novosibirsk, RF).
Target foil was tilted by 30 degree between normal to
target surface and d-beam to reduce distortion of
neutrons emitted from target.
Fully correlated uncertainty 10% for DDX
normalization for thin Li target experiment resulting
from Li foil thickness inaccuracy
